<dl id="n36219e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36219e">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36219e"> 219(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> dispensation of the / fullness of times ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Mormonism.]</font> I have previously alluded to <cite>The Prophecies of Joseph Smith and Their Fulfillment</cite> by Elder Morris &hellip; It is <font color="green">[Morris&apos;s]</font> abiding conviction that &ldquo;we are now in <mark>the Dispensation of the Fullness of Times</mark>.&rdquo; <small> Charles W. Ferguson, <a name="CFCT" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CFCT"><cite title="source">The Confusion of Tongues</cite></a> (1928; rpt. May 1929) 374</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
